    "narrative": "The Austin Waves look to capitalize on several high-upside matchups today, led by **Gunnar Henderson** (83.29) and **Kyle Tucker** (78.73). **Gunnar Henderson** stands as our premier play, benefiting from a massive +16% park factor and a favorable platoon matchup against Landen Roupp, which elevates his offensive potential despite a minor drag from the opposing catcher's pop time. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** is positioned for a breakout performance against Kumar Rocker; with wind blowing out at the venue and a strong order position, he remains a cornerstone of today\u2019s production. **Jackson Merrill** (75.10) also secures a strong rating due to a high-skill matchup against Tomoyuki Sugano and a significant boost from dynamic platoon variables.\n\nSeveral tactical decisions drive the final configuration. **Heliot Ramos** (63.10) and **Andy Pages** (62.85) were prioritized for their high offensive ceilings, specifically benefiting from favorable park dimensions and slow delivery times from their respective opposing pitchers, which facilitates our organizational mandate to target stolen base opportunities. **Josh Lowe** (49.16) remains a marginal start, as he faces a formidable test against the elite stuff of Chase Burns, severely depressing his base projection. On the bench, **Miguel Vargas** (50.99) nearly displaced **Josh Lowe**; however, his lower run-scoring floor against the lefty Kris Bubic kept him sidelined in favor of the higher-upside platoon splits present in the starting nine. We continue to monitor the status of **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Nolan Schanuel**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Nasim Nunez**, and **Josh Jung**, as late-breaking lineup changes could necessitate a pivot for **Marcell Ozuna** or **Liam Hicks** to preserve daily efficiency and game caps. Users should remain alert for \"Lineup Pending\" alerts, particularly regarding **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, whose high scoring projection is heavily contingent on his presumed #3 spot.",
